Object.Field: IKM SQL to JMS XML Append

COMPONENT NAME: IKM SQL to JMS XML Append AUTHOR: Oracle
Description : - Integration Knowledge Module - Inserts data in a JMS XML Message from any ISO-92 compliant staging area.
Restrictions: - The INITIALIZE_XML_SCHEMA option should be set to YES for the first interface loading data in the XML schema. For this interface, ROOT_TABLE should also be set to the resource name of the highest table in the XML model hierarchy, if there is no dedicated interface populating the XML hierarchy root element. - The SYNCHRO_XML_TO_JMS option should be set to YES only for the interface finalizing the loading of the data of the XML schema. - Options: CLIENTID, DURABLE, MESSAGEMAXNUMBER, MESSAGETIMEOUT, MESSAGESELECTOR are not used. They should be set to a null value. - When using this module with a journalized source table, data are automatically filtered to not include source deletions
This option forces the sending of the XML schema as a message in the JMS Topic or Queue. This option should be set to true for the interface finalizing the loading of the XML model.
Initializes the XML structure containing the JMS XML message. Should be set to True for the first interface loading the XML schema.
Resource Name of the XML root

Resource Name of the root datastore element of the XML schema. It is named like the XML file root element. Option applicable only to the first interface loading the schema (when INITIALIZE_XML_SCHEMA=true).
IKM inserts a record for the root element of the XML schema, if ROOT_TABLE<>'' and INITIALIZE_XML_SCHEMA=true. Warning: Use only, if no interface will populate the root table of the XML structure. Otherwise a duplicate root element will be encountered.
Set the JMS Delivery Mode value
Set the JMS Delivery Mode value. 1 = Not Persistent. 2 = Persistent
Expiration delay in milliseconds for the message. 0 = Infinite. 4,000,000 = maximum value
Priority for the message. Any value between 0 (highest priority) and 9 (Lowest priority).
Type of message to send. 1 = BytesMessage. 2 = Text Message
Optional name of the message (data structure)
